CS6114 DECT 6.0 Cordless Phone with Caller ID/Call Waiting

1 Cordless Handset, White/Grey

General Features:

  • DECT 6.0 digital technology.
  • Caller ID/Call Waiting.
  • Backlit keypad and display.
  • 30 name and number phone directory.
  • Volume control.
  • English/Spanish/French setup menus.
Read more

Key Features:

DECT 6.0 Digital Technology

Digitally Enhanced Cordless Telecommunications (DECT) 6.0 is a frequency band that transmits your voice across multiple channels. This technology provides superior quality of voice and sound, high protection against wiretapping and better range than 2.4GHz and 5.8GHz phone systems, while not interfering with wireless routers.

Large, Backlit Display and Keypad

The large display makes it easy to see who is calling, and the the backlit keypad helps you dial in low-light situations.

30 Name and Number Phonebook Directory

Keep all of your important numbers on hand with the 30 number directory.

Read more

Caller ID and Call Waiting

Know who's calling with caller ID/call waiting. The handset displays the name, number, time and date of incoming calls on an easy-to-read backlit display. This phone stores up to 30 calls so you can review who called while you were out.

Desk or Wall-Mountable

The versatile telephone base can be placed on a desk or mounted on the wall.

Compatible with Hearing Aids

TIA-1083 Compliant is a higher standard for cordless phones than just being hearing aid compatible. This standard applies to cordless phones and is especially important when purchasing cordless phones for seniors, as many seniors wear hearing aids.

Read more

      4.0 out of 5 stars Mediocre but makes a great backup handset
      Reviewed in the United States on April 14, 2018
      Color: WhiteStyle: Caller IDVerified Purchase
      The phone deserves three stars but for the low price, it gets four. I purchased this model to connect to an Obi voip box using Google Voice. The family uses cell phones for everything so this is just a backup second line and used sparingly. The phone is as simple as it gets. Menus are basic with few options for customization. Sound quality is fair but usable. A nice feature is the handset locator button on the base which is visible when the phone is removed. The range is sufficient to cover the whole inside of my home. I have not tried walking down the street to see when it drops out.

      A couple negatives - the buttons are hard to push and the base is too light. Dialing too quickly usually results in missing a number. Slow deliberate presses are needed to be sure you dial correctly. The base, even with the phone on charge is very light and topples over easily. Obviously mounting to a wall fixes that. Despite its shortcomings, the phone has been reliable backup for a few months now. I don't think you can find a single cordless handset at a lower price than this. I would buy it again.
